cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.AI 

The paper proposes a novel method for clustering data based on information-theoretic principles, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the conceptual flaws of previous attempts to use information theory for clustering, which could also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces a new clustering measure based on consistency under coarse-graining, which could potentially place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
